# Repository Copilot Instructions

## Purpose
- Apply these standards to all Copilot interactions in this repository.

## Architecture
- Respect existing module boundaries.
- Prefer extending current patterns over introducing new frameworks or abstractions.
- Do not change public contracts unless the task explicitly requires it.

## Code style
- Keep patches small and reviewable.
- Favor readable, idiomatic code over clever shortcuts.
- Reuse existing utility layers before adding new helpers.

## Verification
- Propose verification steps for every non-trivial change.
- Update or add tests when behavior changes.
- Mention any assumptions or unknowns instead of inventing behavior.

## Review expectations
- Call out riskier areas before editing them.
- Summarize changed files and why each changed.
